Thirteen officials were investigated after pictures emerged of scantily-dressed women entertaining inmates. CAPE TOWN - Four warders have been suspended over the &quot;strippers&quot; in prison scandal at the Johannesburg Prison.Thirteen officials were investigated after pictures emerged of scantily-dressed women entertaining inmates.The pictures were reportedly taken during a Youth Day celebration at the prison.The images were widely circulated on social media.The department described the event as unacceptable and a clear breach of security.Correctional Services spokesperson Logan Maistry said: In line with the Labour Relations Act and other Department of Correctional Services policies and regulations at this stage we can confirm that four officials have been suspended and nine others are under consideration. (Edited by Zinhle Nkosi)